Class Encoding

  • java.lang.Object
    • ezvcard.parameter.VCardParameter

  • public class Encoding
extends VCardParameter
    Represents the "ENCODING" parameter.

    Supported versions: 2.1, 3.0

    • Field Detail

      • QUOTED_PRINTABLE

        @SupportedVersions(value=V2_1)
public static final Encoding QUOTED_PRINTABLE
        Note: This specific parameter value is in upper-case in order to resolve a compatibility issue with the Windows 10 Contacts app. The 2.1 spec does not seem to explicitly state that the various ENCODING parameter values are case-insensitive, so this is probably the better approach anyway.
        See Also:
        Issue 56
